[size=130][u]Usage[/u][/size]

Open the map, select a player-owned station, and click the [b]Storage Allocation[/b] tab in the info panel.

[size=125][u]Viewing allocation[/u][/size]

Each storage type row shows a capacity bar with the type name, total space used, and total capacity.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationStorageAllocation/refs/heads/main/docs/images/storage_allocation.png[/img][/spoiler]

Click [b]+[/b] to expand a type and see per-ware rows:
[list]
[*] [b]Stock m³ / %[/b]: current stock and its share of the limit.
[*] [b]Limit m³ / %[/b]: active limit and its share of the type's total capacity.
[*] [b]Auto checkbox[/b]: checked = game manages the limit automatically; unchecked = manually pinned. Click directly to toggle without entering edit mode.
[/list]
The [b]Auto All[/b] button (bottom-left, view mode) clears all manual overrides for the currently expanded type in one click. It is only enabled when at least one ware has a manual override.

[size=125][u]Edit mode[/u][/size]

Click [b]Edit[/b] to enter edit mode (game pauses).

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationStorageAllocation/refs/heads/main/docs/images/edit_mode.png[/img][/spoiler]

A slider appears for each ware in the expanded type. Slide to adjust the allocation - other wares adjust proportionally to stay within capacity. The saved (game) limit is shown greyed-out above the slider for reference.
[list]
[*] [b]Ignore stock[/b]: enables setting a limit below current stock. Auto-enabled when any ware's saved limit is already below its stock.
[/list]
[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationStorageAllocation/refs/heads/main/docs/images/edit_mode_ignore_stock.png[/img][/spoiler]
[list]
[*] [b]Reset All[/b]: removes all manual overrides on the station, restoring fully auto-managed limits.
[*] [b]Save[/b]: applies all slider values and exits edit mode (game resumes).
[*] [b]Cancel[/b]: discards all changes and exits edit mode (game resumes).
[/list]
[size=125][u]Extension options[/u][/size]

[b]Options Menu > Extension options > Station Storage Allocation[/b]:

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationStorageAllocation/refs/heads/main/docs/images/options.png[/img][/spoiler]
[list]
[*] [b]Stock cache refresh interval[/b] (1-10, default 3): UI ticks before stock values are re-read from the game. Lower = more up-to-date, higher = less CPU usage.
[/list]
